TI  - Real-Time Integrated Berth–Quay Crane Scheduling Decision Model via Deep Q-Learning and Adaptive Large Neighborhood Search
AU  - J. Xu
AU  - J. Yang
T2  - 2025 10th International Conference on Information Science, Computer Technology and Transportation (ISCTT)
AB  - In the port and terminal logistics system port and quay crane scheduling is very complex and difficult challenging and efficient effective collaboration coordination between berths schedules and quay cranes schedules is very important. To address this issue, this paper presents a port-berth-quay crane joint scheduling decision-making real-time model based on deep Q learning and adaptive large neighborhood search. The model is developed from the traditional berth allocation and quay crane scheduling model and a new methodology is proposed here and further a multi-agent reinforcement learning framework is applied, in which each agent is a berth-quay crane cooperation system. The DQL module can effectively learn the optimal scheduling policy adaptively while the ship's arrival time and operation time are random in the uncertain environment. Meanwhile, the adaptive large neighborhood search structure efficiently escapes the local optimal solution space by utilizing perturbation and repair strategies in conjunction with historical reward trajectory and action entropy. To enhance the learning efficiency and decision-making robustness of the model, we also propose a hybrid reward shaping mechanism and a two-layer time abstraction template to handle the problems of high-dimensional state space and delayed feedback. Experimental results demonstrate model port dataset remarkably outperforms baseline approaches and learning-based methods in terms of total turnaround time, resource utilization and decision delay.
