TI  - A Hybrid Deep Reinforcement Learning and Graph Neural Network Approach for Multi-objective Waste Transportation Optimization
AU  - L. Gao
AU  - W. Xing
T2  - 2025 8th International Conference on Algorithms, Computing and Artificial Intelligence (ACAI)
AB  - With the increasing amount of urban waste generated, optimizing and scheduling waste transportation routes has become a major challenge in the development of smart cities. This paper proposes a method based on combining deep reinforcement learning (PPO) with graph neural networks (GNNs) to address the path planning and scheduling problem in urban waste transportation. By combining PPO with GNNs, this study is able to optimize the transportation routes and vehicle scheduling strategies for multiple types of waste within a multi-objective optimization framework that considers transportation costs, carbon emissions, and computational efficiency. Experimental results demonstrate that the proposed method significantly outperforms traditional integer programming (IP), genetic algorithm (GA), and particle swarm optimization (PSO) methods in terms of transportation cost and carbon emissions control, while maintaining a stable computational time growth and exhibiting strong scalability and robustness. This study provides an innovative solution to the waste transportation scheduling problem in smart cities and has important practical implications for future green logistics and sustainable urban development.
