TI  - Large Vehicle Scheduling Based on Uncertainty Weighting Harmonic Twin-Critic Network
AU  - X. Huang
AU  - K. Yang
AU  - J. Ling
T2  - IEEE Systems Journal
AB  - Large-scale online car-hailing platforms have greatly improved travel efficiency by dispatching orders quickly. However, effectively scheduling vehicles for a large-scale fleet is a challenging task for car-hailing platforms. Currently, the most popular methods for solving vehicle scheduling are reinforcement learning-based approaches. However, existing vehicle scheduling algorithms often overestimate the Q-value of an action due to the presence of out-of-distribution (OOD) data in the training datasets. Therefore, reasonable estimation of the action value is an important research problem in reinforcement learning. To address this problem, this article proposes a multiagent reinforcement learning algorithm to optimize the estimation of the Q-value, called the uncertainty weighting harmonic twin-critic (UWTC) algorithm. The UWTC algorithm is able to improve the scheduling efficiency of vehicles by reducing the influence of OOD data through the use of an uncertainty weighting module and a harmonic network. Extensive experiments were conducted on a dataset of DiDi in Chengdu, and the experimental results show that the UWTC algorithm achieves the best results in terms of both the average response rate of orders and the revenue of the platforms.
