TI  - A Graph Neural Network-Based Method for Dynamic Path Scheduling in AGV Systems
AU  - H. Ma
AU  - Y. Feng
AU  - H. Shi
T2  - 2025 9th International Symposium on Computer Science and Intelligent Control (ISCSIC)
AB  - With the increasing application of Automated Guided Vehicles (AGVs) in intelligent manufacturing, an increasing number of smart workshops rely on AGV systems for material handling and distribution. However, traditional AGV scheduling methods, often based on fixed rules or heuristic algorithms, struggle to adapt effectively to real-world scenarios involving multiple tasks and dynamically complex environments. To address these challenges, this paper proposes an improved AGV material distribution algorithm based on Graph Neural Networks (GNN). The proposed approach models the workshop environment as a graph structure and utilizes Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) to deeply extract features from nodes and paths, enabling task node probability prediction and route smoothness scoring. Based on this, a multi-AGV collision-free path planning and conflict avoidance mechanism is designed, taking into account both static priorities and dynamic operational states. This allows for reasonable task sequencing and assignment, ensuring real-time path planning and efficient execution during multi-vehicle collaboration. Simulation experiments under various dynamic multi-task scenarios demonstrate that the proposed method outperforms traditional approaches in task completion efficiency, providing a practical and scalable solution for intelligent workshop scheduling.
