AB  - Urban taxi systems struggle to manage their fleets in real time and often cannot integrate with other modes of transportation or adapt to changing conditions. We propose a hybrid reinforcement learning framework that includes Q-learning and rule-based optimization to schedule a taxis fleet optimization that can utilize multiple modes of the transportation. The framework contains real-time weather’s fluctuations and the behaviour of the passengers how they are acting to make fixed-route transit work in a better way. The experimental demonstrations illustrate a 23.4% increase in performance over random scheduling technique, with which vehicle utilisation and an average wait time of 0.42 hours are improved, even when the environment is uncertain.
