TI  - High Precision Passive Positioning System and Intelligent Charging Scheduling Strategy for Electric Vehicle Charging Station Based on Visible Light
AU  - Y. Zhao
AU  - W. Wang
AU  - Y. Yu
AU  - M. Li
AU  - S. Gu
AU  - J. Hu
AU  - Y. Guo
T2  - 2025 IEEE 10th International Conference on Data Science in Cyberspace (DSC)
AB  - How to achieve efficient coordination of charging resources during peak charging hours has become an urgent problem to be solved in the electric vehicle industry at this stage. Designing the optimal charging navigation map for electric vehicles to be charged is a manifestation of reasonable vehicle scheduling at charging stations. Therefore, positioning technology is the key research to solve the “last meter” problem of charging navigation. In addition, charging scheduling should be a dynamic standard, which should be adjusted continuously with changes in factors such as power generation and actual conditions in the station. To this end, this paper conducts research on charging station positioning technology and intelligent charging scheduling technology around the above problems. This paper first proposes a charging station vehicle positioning system based on visible light passive positioning, and then designs a positioning network based on convolutional recurrent network (CRNN)-Kolmogorov-Arnold Network (KAN). And construct an intelligent charging scheduling framework with comprehensive positioning navigation, charging load balancing and carbon emission optimization. We conducted simulation experiments on the positioning method, and the experimental results show that the method can achieve centimeter-level positioning, and the probability of error below 0.5m reaches 80%. It proves that the positioning CRNN-KAN network proposed in this problem has good reliability.
