AU  - X. Shao
T2  - 2025 3rd International Conference on Logistics Engineering, Supply Chain and Digital Transformation (LESCDT)
AB  - With the deep integration of artificial intelligence (AI) and the Internet of Things (IoT) technology in warehousing and logistics, the widespread application of automated warehousing equipment such as mobile robot fulfillment systems (RMFS) and automated guided vehicles (AGV) has significantly improved the efficiency of warehouse operations. However, in high concurrency order scenarios, traditional path planning methods still face severe challenges. This article proposes a multi-objective path intelligent scheduling framework for smart logistics that integrates reinforcement learning (RL). This framework adopts a hierarchical collaborative decision-making mechanism: for the picking process of orders in the warehouse, a joint optimization problem of order allocation and AGV scheduling (IOARSP) is proposed, aiming to minimize the overall completion time of a batch of orders and improve the system's operational efficiency. A multi-agent RL based delivery path scheduling (MRLRS) strategy was designed for the logistics distribution process after outbound shipment. This strategy models delivery path scheduling as a path generation process, iteratively generates paths using an encoder decoder framework with attention mechanism, and designs a multiagent RL training method that integrates unsupervised auxiliary networks. Simulation experiments show that the proposed algorithm can effectively cope with high concurrency dynamic requirements.
